Package: MRGxE
Title: Genome-to-Genome Interaction Screening via Mendelian Randomization
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Xiaofeng", "Zhu", role = c("aut"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0000-0000-0000")),
    person("Yihe", "Yang", role = c("aut")),
    person("Chen", "et al.", role = c("ctb")),
    person(given = "Maintainer", role = "cre",
           email = "maintainer@example.com")
  )
Description: Implements a generalized MR-based interaction screening framework
    for detecting pairwise interactions between two genomic entities (e.g.,
    gene-environment, host-pathogen, gene-gene). Based on the observation that
    the relationship between two related sets of genetic effect estimates (e.g.,
    GWAS marginal effect vs GWIS main effect) follows a linear regression, and
    variants with interaction or mediation effects systematically deviate from
    this line. The framework encompasses:
    (1) GxE screening as in Zhu et al. (2024) Nature Communications
        <doi:10.1038/s41467-024-47806-3>;
    (2) Host-pathogen genome-to-genome interaction screening as in Chen et al.
        (2026) Nature, "EBV strain interacts with host HLA to drive
        nasopharyngeal carcinoma risk".
    Supports summary-statistics and individual-level data inputs, multiple
    study designs, permutation-based significance testing, conditional analysis,
    and flexible modular pipelines.
